Body relatively slender, BW 7.2 mm (BW/SVL ratio 0.22 ); head indistinct from neck and from body; 42 paravertebral rows; 49 ventrals; skin fragile; body scales cycloid, with 2 feeble keels; 32 transverse scale rows at midbody; 58 subcaudals; on dorsum, keels start from the nuchals; scales on flanks with weak keels; scales on venter smooth, uniform in size except the median ventral scales being relatively enlarged than those on the flanks; each ventral scale shows at an angle two faint notches on the anterior margin and one notch on the posterior margin; preanals enlarged, lateral pair of preanals overlap median preanal; tail long (TL/SVL ratio 1.33 ), tip acute, tail base wider than rest of tail, gradually tapering to a point; median row of subcaudals not enlarged relative to adjacent scales. Limbs relatively short; pentadactyl and clawed; scales on limbs weakly bicarinate; lamellae obtusely tuberculate and enlarged; adpressed limbs reach up to middle of the forearm; lamellae under Finger
